<br>
This is an attitude you seem to share with Verant.  It's a bad attitude and it's a big part of the problem.  A lot of people <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> have</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> quit their mages because they got tired of waiting for fixes.  Some of us are a lot more tenacious and unwilling to spend time on another class that may simply also get nerfed.<br>
<br>
Mages have gone from damage dealing powerhouses to utility mana-batteries.  Why should I switch to a wizard, spend all that time getting him to 60 when they may be next on the list for nerf batting?  I'll leave <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> that</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> kind of move to the suckers of the world.<br>
<br>
Don't forget that once upon a time, mages could hand their pets low delay weapons and the pets would use the delay but retain their normal damage-per-swing.  THOSE were the good old days.  Warriors using their uber Ykeshas (&quot;Y-whats?&quot;) or, rarely, uber-uber-Bloodfire, couldn't hope to compete.<br>
<br>
These days, our pets do less damage and you can't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> give</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Ykeshas away.  Twinks already have better stuff off of lower level Kunark mobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> (shaman/enchanter/druid/bard/necro/shadowknight all DEBUFF better then we do overall). <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
lol, yeah, those SK debuffs!  Whoa!  We can't do raids without them around.<br>
<br>
I agree with your underlying principle, that mages are far weaker than they should be, but let's try to stay loosely in reality.<br>
<br>
IMO, the one big change Verant needs to do is a universal upgrade of our pets, starting at level 4 and ending with the magician epic pet.  Every single one needs to have it's damage re-evaluated compared to same level melee characters with appropriate level equipment.<br>
<br>
It was balanced 3 years ago, but a lot has changed since then, and it needs to be rebalanced across ALL levels.<br>
