<br>
You don't always have to waste your mana on a big fight on mod rods...nuke away...enjoy yourself...its fun.  Summon the mod rods before the fight.  Make sure the entire raid party has one in their inventory, and drops them before the fight.  With mod rod 2 and a 40 man raid...that is 27,000 more mana added to the fight by the mage/s.  How is that not useful?  Not to mention you get to use your mana during the fight for much needed damage, unlike the necro who has to sit there and feed directly in the fight.  <br>
<br>
Mod rod 2 is a godsend spell for mages.  My guild generally find mod rods just as pressing or even moreso at times as having all the melees buffed and ready.  After every tough fight we win...there is generally a resounding &quot;OMG, I LOVE MAGES&quot; from all the clerics, because they wouldn't have been able to keep the CH circle going without that boatload of mod rods on the ground.  And don't say just add another cleric instead of a mage.  5 clerics + 1 mage that has dropped 27,000 mana on the ground &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 6 clerics BY FAR!!  We are an excellent support class...GOD people, when will you see that?<br>
