<br>
I could say the same thing about you.  Substitute &quot;content&quot; with &quot;unhappy&quot;. I believe I have addressed the utility of mages in full...but I'll recap<br>
<br>
1.) COH - By far, the most useful spell we are given.  Some raids I'm on would take hours of just getting the raid to the fight spot...not to mention not being able to add others to the crew after everything is already set up.<br>
<br>
2.) Mod Rods - I won't go in to this again...read above posts<br>
<br>
3.) Debuffing - A lvl 60 mage is just as effective as a lvl 60 shaman in magic debuffing a mob with mala/malosini combo as opposed to malo/malosini combo (Note I say &quot;magic debuffing&quot;.  A shaman blows everyone away with their melee debuffing with slow spells and cripple.)<br>
<br>
4.) I have yet to start a big fight where the Main Tank does not ask one of the mages for a DS.  On mobs with fire AE, I generally get /tells from multiple groups asking for a DS, and with /targetg, I happily oblige<br>
<br>
5.) Don't fool yourself into believing we are not valued for our summons.  I am constantly getting tells throughout a raid for various summons...unlike most mages...I love this.  Half the reason I made a mage was to be able to conjure up little knick knacks...if just for a role-play issue.  It's very cool to know that I can offer something with that ability.<br>
<br>
That's five things.  Fool yourself into believing that any one utility class (Enchanter/Shaman/Druid etc.) have more to do than 5-6 different things in any one raid, and I can see where you would get upset.  Many make the arguement that these things are not vital to a raid, and I'd make the same arguement about any of the other utility classes for certain raids.  Utility is about making a raid go smoothly...which is JUST as important as getting the raid going at all.  IMHO, I'd rather just not raid if its not going to be a smooth one.  Now if you're not happy with these roles, than I can't argue with you, but its YOU who must face up to the fact that we do, in fact, have utility.  I enjoy my role, I do it well, I let people know about what I can do..no..I FORCE people to know what I can do..and they love me for it.  I am never told I'm not needed by any one of them...in fact, its really quite the opposite..when I log on, they want me where they are, cause they know I will be bringing the value of a well played utility mage to the table.  I ask you...what do YOU bring to a raid besides sulking and bitching?<br>
<br>
Now on to your fact two...hey you're right.  We no longer deal damage like we used to.  We can't KS an entire raid anymore (ok..I have recently with sirocco, but that was situational <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ), but we do deal damage when we so desire.  Case in point...I was in a TOV farming session in a group with a cleric/paladin/druid/and shaman I believe (might have been a warrior instead of druid..I don't remember).  Well...we were far from the KS group.  Monk pulls an ice wurm, and I make a snyde comment in group about getting exp on this one.  I cast sirocco 4 times I believe.  It hits for full almost every wave and I end up doing probably around 6k damage to the thing in a relatively short amount of time.  Our group got the exp <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Another example of how we can use our damage....I was attending a Lendi the Keeper raid.  She got to around 40 life...I looked around and there were still some mod rods down from the initial drop because the fight was going textbook well, so I decide to step out and nuke instead of mod rodding.   Oh did I mention that I hit her with malosini at the start of the fight? (but that has to do with utility <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )  Well I step out and hit her with about 12 - 57 shocks. None of them were fully resisted, and I venture to say I did about 7k-8k damage to her.  Its not great, but its damage...and its damage that we're able to dish out after we've performed all of our utility tasks.  We're not wanted for our damage..that is true..we're wanted for our utility (at least I am), but we can add damage when we wish.<br>
<br>
You complain about soloing as your third fact.  I ask you to back up your arguement that we no longer rank in the top half.  With a full bar of mana I kill (give or take) 7-8 mobs depending on the particular mob it is.  Then I sit down and regen my mana nicely with a brand new self only mana regen buff we were given with Luclin.  I med for 6-8 minutes to full, and spend the next 20 minutes to half an hour killing those 8 mobs again.  That's not alot of downtime respectively.  I can easily say I spend more time on my feet fighting than I do medding these days when I'm solo.  That is a direct contridiction to how it was when I was supposedly in the top half of soloists.  You tell me I'm not a good soloists anymore...that's news to me....I think I do fine.  In fact, for the first time in a good long time, I'm getting better exp solo than in some groups.<br>
<br>
Blah...I've spent far too long arguing this.  But I've made my point.  I've backed up my claims.  I enjoy my roles.  You don't.  That's what it boils down to.  You can write me off saying I've done nothing and that I'm still just giving 'fluff', but that'd be pretty lame of you....but I guess you're used to being lame because you play such a lame class, right?<br>
