<br>
Being Lvl 40, I can't use experience (obviously) from attending plane raids or the higher level areas, so If you're a stickler for facts and data crunching offensive efficiency is your mantra, my words will probably mean even far less.<br>
<br>
On that note, I think that some players are too enveloped in the idea that Verant somehow actually works for it's consumers.  The basic fact for the groundwork of EQ is time=money.  The more time you spend playing EQ, the more money Verant/Sony gets.<br>
<br>
Now, if Verant is able (*cough* willing) to make our well-known biggest issues solvent, then where does that leave them?  They've replaced their addicted-disgruntled consumers into content- and arguably, BORED players.  Verant will never shoot themselves in the foot like that.  <br>
Dev_team_00 says: &quot;Cripes, let's make this work like they want it.&quot;<br>
Corporate_suit has slain Dev_team_00.<br>
Corporate_suit says: &quot;Ignorance.  They'll leave us.&quot;<br>
<br>
And you would leave.  Because fact of the matter is if we had nothing to bitch about, and we didn't have a reason to vent at Verant, then we'd become detached from &quot;our&quot; game.  We'd start looking for something new.  City of Heroes, Galaxies, etc.  Something that we could have a &quot;say&quot; in.  Because this game is valuable to us.  <br>
<br>
You and I probably put more time into it then we'd admit to our family.  And that underlying value to us keeps us coming back.  But if it were all well and good, and there were no class issues, then it just wouldn't be as interesting....<br>
<br>
or fun.<br>
<br>
Therefore, for as much bitching and whining as you hear from any class, and especially mages in general I leave you with this..<br>
<br>
$#it or get off the pot.<br>
<br>
You don't like how stuffs goin'?...Leave.  Go raise your blasters and lightsabers in Galaxies.  Cause nothing's really gonna change.  There will still be massive &quot;problems&quot; in this game.  Because that's how Verant wants it.<br>
<br>
And that's how it should be.  Imperfect.  It will never be balanced.  And I am fine with it.<br>
<br>
/chucks 2 cp down and gnaws on some gator meat. <p>Deviction Xue <BR> 
lvl 40 ChainCasterMaster<BR>
