And Grumples...I couldn't disagree with your list more. First off a lvl 60 shaman is WAY up there. With torpor/cann/manaless DoT/DD, slow, buffs...they are a soloing machine. lvl 60 Necromancers with root/DoT soloing strategy has nearly no downtime. lvl 60 Monk with fungi could solo an entire dungeon...and I really do not consider Bards and Druids to be up there. <br>
