I assume your using your 58 shock, at 8 seconds a pop thats 12x8 1min 36 seconds to 57x8 7 min 36 seconds? am I interpreting this information correctly? you don't remember how many you got off but it was between 12-57 while chain casting and standing in the aoe the whole time of course.<br>
<br>
As for mod rods vs. necro pumping, there very different server different purposes, necro pumping is faster, safer and of more use during most fights, mod rods reduce downtime and are also a form of mana storage. If I had to choose one or the other it would probably be mod rod 2 but thats certienly not true of everyone. BTW I was one of the mages to give the biggest cheer over this spell, its simply incredible and I have no doubt that after VI has some of luclins bugs fixed it will be in the first round of nerfing along with dire charm.<br>
<br>
As for us being on par with shamans for resistance debuffing, well imperically we are not, FACT we simply do not debuff to the same degree they do on our top of the line resistance debuff. Although I will admit in resistance debuffing we are both valide and useful. BTW I would like to thank you for implying that were a utility class on par with enchanters/shamans/druids I am sure that you just entertained many people and not just me.<br>
<br>
Some of you seem to question what I put, well here we go.<br>
<br>
First off, for damage, damage is different in every situation, I am talking about end game(as I always am as its where I play). Put a mage at 60 with epic bboots/kt boots blah blah whatever dream equipment you want next to a warrior/monk/rogue/sk/paladin/ranger all equiped with primal or better weapons. I suggest that every mage do this on there own to learn for themselves just how far behind we are. My personal logs show mages approx on par with meleeing bards on average(there is a very large range which we fall into however because mages are affected to a huge degree by which mob we fight).<br>
<br>
My second point when I say utility classes I mean utility classes, shamans/enchanters/druids/Sk's I could include monks here simply for FD. We do not compare to these classes in any way shape or form for combat utility(hell we don't compare to ANYONE for combat utility).<br>
<br>
Soloing, this is rather straight forward, given a top 25% spot for any paticular class who will solo with A) the most gain and B) the most safty. Quite simply who soloes most efficently for XP as this is the only real use of soloing in the end game.(there simply is no equipment in the game that can be taken off a soloable mob that my character would use). You talk about having 8 minutes of downtime after fighting 7-8 blue mobs(there are many blue mobs that would rip your pet to 5% and leave you with 10% mana, so please specify exactly which mobs your talking about because I would really like to know your secret, obvioulsy your a better soloer then me) and you seem to think that compares to virtual 0 downtime for necro's/monks/paladins noticebly less downtime for warriors/rogues/sks, same downtime for wizards/druids(a little less actually) but with FAR more saftey then we have.<br>
